00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:12.411 align:middle line:90%


00:01:12.411 --> 00:01:17.410 align:middle line:90%
[INSECTS CHIRP AND FROG CROAKS]

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:19.620 align:middle line:84%
>>We're here in Central
America to search

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:22.720 align:middle line:84%
for ancient technology in
Nicaragua and Costa Rica.

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:27.202 align:middle line:90%
[ANIMAL SOUNDS]

00:01:27.202 --> 00:01:36.680 align:middle line:90%


00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:40.440 align:middle line:84%
We've seen some amazing
ancient technology in Egypt

00:01:40.440 --> 00:01:44.740 align:middle line:84%
and further evidence of ancient
technology in Peru and Bolivia.

00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:48.240 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:48.240 --> 00:02:16.170 align:middle line:90%


00:02:16.170 --> 00:02:19.940 align:middle line:84%
I then decided we needed to
investigate the many mysteries

00:02:19.940 --> 00:02:23.300 align:middle line:84%
of Central America and
the possible evidence

00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:28.350 align:middle line:84%
for advanced ancient
technology in that region.

00:02:28.350 --> 00:02:31.990 align:middle line:84%
Our first stop was the capital
of Costa Rica, San Jose.

00:02:31.990 --> 00:02:34.960 align:middle line:90%


00:02:34.960 --> 00:02:37.600 align:middle line:84%
It was in San Jose
that I was very

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:42.040 align:middle line:84%
curious about the
giant stone balls that

00:02:42.040 --> 00:02:45.770 align:middle line:84%
have been found in the
southwestern part of Costa

00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:46.810 align:middle line:90%
Rica.

00:02:46.810 --> 00:02:51.430 align:middle line:84%
Many of these balls are
huge, bigger than a car.

00:02:51.430 --> 00:02:56.100 align:middle line:84%
And they've been moved
to certain parks that

00:02:56.100 --> 00:03:01.213 align:middle line:84%
are in San Jose, where people
can view these megalithic stone

00:03:01.213 --> 00:03:02.013 align:middle line:90%
balls.

00:03:02.013 --> 00:03:05.190 align:middle line:90%


00:03:05.190 --> 00:03:12.430 align:middle line:84%
I was really curious as to how
these stone balls were made.

00:03:12.430 --> 00:03:14.700 align:middle line:84%
My experiences with
Christopher Dunn

00:03:14.700 --> 00:03:21.740 align:middle line:84%
showed me that the ancients
had some kind of power tools

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:25.710 align:middle line:84%
and engineering capabilities
much like we have today.

00:03:25.710 --> 00:03:32.300 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, the machining of
these perfectly spherical stone

00:03:32.300 --> 00:03:37.920 align:middle line:84%
balls is something that is so
difficult it could really only

00:03:37.920 --> 00:03:42.090 align:middle line:90%
be done with power tools.

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:45.430 align:middle line:84%
Despite the fact that
these megalithic stone

00:03:45.430 --> 00:03:49.440 align:middle line:84%
balls are found
throughout Costa Rica,

00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:52.500 align:middle line:84%
the various museums
and publications

00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:56.070 align:middle line:84%
give no idea of what the
purpose was of these balls

00:03:56.070 --> 00:03:57.650 align:middle line:84%
or even how they
were constructed.

00:03:57.650 --> 00:04:04.620 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.620 --> 00:04:07.470 align:middle line:84%
This granite ball here
at the National Museum

00:04:07.470 --> 00:04:12.000 align:middle line:84%
in San Jose, Costa Rica is
one of the better specimens.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:14.721 align:middle line:90%
It's perfectly round.

00:04:14.721 --> 00:04:16.269 align:middle line:90%
It's quite a large ball.

00:04:16.269 --> 00:04:22.630 align:middle line:84%
It probably weighs several tons,
possibly even up to 10 tons.

00:04:22.630 --> 00:04:26.300 align:middle line:84%
It's been carved out
of a very hard granite.

00:04:26.300 --> 00:04:31.040 align:middle line:84%
And it's an exquisite piece
of megalithic architecture.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:33.900 align:middle line:84%
But once again, the
purpose of these balls

00:04:33.900 --> 00:04:38.120 align:middle line:84%
and even how they were
made remains a mystery

00:04:38.120 --> 00:04:38.920 align:middle line:90%
to archeologists.

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:45.120 align:middle line:90%


00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:47.970 align:middle line:84%
One of the theories
on Atlantis is

00:04:47.970 --> 00:04:54.610 align:middle line:84%
that Atlantis was, around 10,000
BC, a worldwide civilization,

00:04:54.610 --> 00:04:57.100 align:middle line:90%
a maritime civilization.

00:04:57.100 --> 00:05:01.790 align:middle line:84%
They left their capital city
of Atlantis, and in the ships,

00:05:01.790 --> 00:05:05.580 align:middle line:84%
went all over the world,
going to the Americas,

00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:10.100 align:middle line:84%
to Africa, to Europe,
and to all continents.

00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:12.790 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the
mysteries of Atlantis

00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:17.740 align:middle line:90%
is these giant stone balls.

00:05:17.740 --> 00:05:19.650 align:middle line:84%
These giant granite
balls are often

00:05:19.650 --> 00:05:22.680 align:middle line:90%
associated with the Atlanteans.

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:25.680 align:middle line:84%
They're found on
many continents,

00:05:25.680 --> 00:05:28.290 align:middle line:84%
especially here in
Central America.

00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:31.400 align:middle line:84%
But these giant stone balls
have been found in Malta.

00:05:31.400 --> 00:05:34.890 align:middle line:84%
They've been found on remote
islands such as Easter Island.

00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:37.630 align:middle line:84%
There's an area of New
Zealand that also has

00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:39.476 align:middle line:90%
round stone balls like this.

00:05:39.476 --> 00:05:42.810 align:middle line:90%


00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:46.960 align:middle line:84%
Another big question with
these giant stone balls

00:05:46.960 --> 00:05:49.970 align:middle line:90%
is what they were for.

00:05:49.970 --> 00:05:52.810 align:middle line:90%
It's baffling to archeologists.

00:05:52.810 --> 00:05:59.030 align:middle line:84%
Why anyone would go through
considerable effort,

00:05:59.030 --> 00:06:04.390 align:middle line:84%
even if they had power tools,
to make these giant stone balls.

00:06:04.390 --> 00:06:06.750 align:middle line:90%
I mean what is the point?

00:06:06.750 --> 00:06:11.550 align:middle line:84%
Today, mainstream
archeologists are just

00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:15.950 align:middle line:84%
grasping at straws for
some kind of explanation.

00:06:15.950 --> 00:06:19.210 align:middle line:84%
Their main explanation
right now is

00:06:19.210 --> 00:06:22.710 align:middle line:84%
that these giant stone
balls-- and some of them

00:06:22.710 --> 00:06:27.660 align:middle line:84%
are relatively small, only
the size of a basketball

00:06:27.660 --> 00:06:28.630 align:middle line:90%
or a little bit bigger.

00:06:28.630 --> 00:06:32.776 align:middle line:84%
While others are five,
six feet in diameter--

00:06:32.776 --> 00:06:35.850 align:middle line:84%
that they are some kind
of ceremonial object.

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:39.930 align:middle line:84%
And they have found some
of the smaller stone balls

00:06:39.930 --> 00:06:42.120 align:middle line:90%
in tombs in Costa Rica.

00:06:42.120 --> 00:06:49.120 align:middle line:84%
And it's like important chiefs,
or kings, or shamans were

00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:52.430 align:middle line:90%
buried with these stone balls--

00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:54.470 align:middle line:90%
generally the small ones.

00:06:54.470 --> 00:06:57.620 align:middle line:84%
But still, it doesn't
really explain what

00:06:57.620 --> 00:06:59.165 align:middle line:90%
these stone balls were for.

00:06:59.165 --> 00:07:01.900 align:middle line:90%


00:07:01.900 --> 00:07:05.800 align:middle line:84%
It's my theory that
these stone balls

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:11.420 align:middle line:84%
that are found in the
tombs and burials of some

00:07:11.420 --> 00:07:16.150 align:middle line:84%
of these important people
in ancient Costa Rica,

00:07:16.150 --> 00:07:19.730 align:middle line:84%
that they didn't know what
these balls were for either.

00:07:19.730 --> 00:07:24.850 align:middle line:84%
And that these balls are many,
many thousands of years old.

00:07:24.850 --> 00:07:31.070 align:middle line:84%
They apparently washed up
like by some tidal wave

00:07:31.070 --> 00:07:35.100 align:middle line:84%
that hit the southwest
coast of Costa Rica.

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:38.620 align:middle line:84%
And it literally
washed these balls up

00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:43.060 align:middle line:84%
into mountain jungle areas,
onto one of the islands that's

00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:44.392 align:middle line:90%
off the coast of Costa Rica.

00:07:44.392 --> 00:07:46.940 align:middle line:90%


00:07:46.940 --> 00:07:49.360 align:middle line:84%
The ancient people
of Costa Rica,

00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:53.770 align:middle line:84%
who are then using
these balls as some kind

00:07:53.770 --> 00:07:59.370 align:middle line:84%
of ceremonial object,
didn't actually

00:07:59.370 --> 00:08:01.610 align:middle line:84%
build them or
machine these balls.

00:08:01.610 --> 00:08:04.130 align:middle line:84%
They're finding them
in the jungle thinking

00:08:04.130 --> 00:08:08.730 align:middle line:84%
they are some kind
of eggs of the gods

00:08:08.730 --> 00:08:13.390 align:middle line:84%
or giant stone
balls of the gods.

00:08:13.390 --> 00:08:15.350 align:middle line:84%
And then the small ones,
just because they're

00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:20.660 align:middle line:84%
some oddball important object,
are buried with these chiefs.

00:08:20.660 --> 00:08:22.150 align:middle line:84%
But they didn't
make these balls.

00:08:22.150 --> 00:08:25.820 align:middle line:90%
They were already there.

00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:30.210 align:middle line:84%
So you have to ask yourself,
who made these balls,

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:33.450 align:middle line:90%
and what was their function?

00:08:33.450 --> 00:08:36.919 align:middle line:84%
This is something that we
really haven't figured out.

00:08:36.919 --> 00:08:41.470 align:middle line:84%
My idea is that these balls are
from many thousands of years

00:08:41.470 --> 00:08:42.270 align:middle line:90%
ago.

00:08:42.270 --> 00:08:46.210 align:middle line:84%
The same people
who were building

00:08:46.210 --> 00:08:51.350 align:middle line:84%
at Tiwanaku, and at Cusco, and
Oyente Tambo, and Machu Picchu,

00:08:51.350 --> 00:08:55.320 align:middle line:84%
and other megalith areas
of Peru and Bolivia,

00:08:55.320 --> 00:09:02.110 align:middle line:84%
were a similar people as to
those in Central America,

00:09:02.110 --> 00:09:04.110 align:middle line:84%
including perhaps
the Olmecs, who

00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:05.620 align:middle line:84%
were building the
colossal basalt

00:09:05.620 --> 00:09:10.340 align:middle line:84%
heads and other giant
megalithic artifacts

00:09:10.340 --> 00:09:13.930 align:middle line:90%
that we can find there.

00:09:13.930 --> 00:09:16.780 align:middle line:84%
And they, with their
machine tools--

00:09:16.780 --> 00:09:20.420 align:middle line:84%
and I believe the Olmecs
had machining tools,

00:09:20.420 --> 00:09:23.450 align:middle line:84%
as were used in Egypt, as were
used in Peru, and Bolivia,

00:09:23.450 --> 00:09:26.930 align:middle line:90%
and other areas of the world.

00:09:26.930 --> 00:09:28.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was through
this that they were

00:09:28.770 --> 00:09:30.640 align:middle line:90%
making these giant stone balls.

00:09:30.640 --> 00:09:33.340 align:middle line:84%
We still don't know
exactly what they're for.

00:09:33.340 --> 00:09:38.750 align:middle line:84%
Theories say that they were
possibly used by navigators.

00:09:38.750 --> 00:09:45.680 align:middle line:84%
And that by placing these stone
balls in positions together,

00:09:45.680 --> 00:09:48.840 align:middle line:84%
were showing where
islands were for people

00:09:48.840 --> 00:09:51.500 align:middle line:84%
who were crossing the Pacific,
or crossing the Atlantic,

00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:58.070 align:middle line:84%
and in transoceanic
trading expeditions,

00:09:58.070 --> 00:10:00.560 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:10:00.560 --> 00:10:05.320 align:middle line:84%
So that's one idea, that these
huge stone balls were all part

00:10:05.320 --> 00:10:08.310 align:middle line:90%
of an elaborate map system.

00:10:08.310 --> 00:10:10.180 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps too, they
were showing where

00:10:10.180 --> 00:10:13.370 align:middle line:90%
stars were and constellations.

00:10:13.370 --> 00:10:16.460 align:middle line:84%
In my mind, that's a
pretty interesting theory.

00:10:16.460 --> 00:10:21.000 align:middle line:84%
However, I don't think it
explains the really, really

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:24.830 align:middle line:84%
large stone balls very
well, because they

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:27.660 align:middle line:90%
are so huge and so heavy.

00:10:27.660 --> 00:10:31.230 align:middle line:84%
And it would have been so
difficult to make those.

00:10:31.230 --> 00:10:35.760 align:middle line:84%
It seems like it would have
been a lot of extra effort

00:10:35.760 --> 00:10:38.350 align:middle line:84%
that would be quite
unnecessary if you're just

00:10:38.350 --> 00:10:43.460 align:middle line:84%
trying to create star
maps and navigation

00:10:43.460 --> 00:10:45.510 align:middle line:90%
maps of islands and things.

00:10:45.510 --> 00:10:50.180 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't need a giant stone
balls for that in my mind.

00:10:50.180 --> 00:10:53.280 align:middle line:84%
Today, these balls from the
swamps of southwestern Costa

00:10:53.280 --> 00:10:56.540 align:middle line:84%
Rica are scattered
around the country.

00:10:56.540 --> 00:10:59.750 align:middle line:84%
They're found in bank
lawns, in museums, and even

00:10:59.750 --> 00:11:01.910 align:middle line:90%
in private homes.

00:11:01.910 --> 00:11:06.679 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:06.679 --> 00:11:35.040 align:middle line:90%


00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:38.150 align:middle line:84%
We're deep in the jungles of
Central Costa Rico at the lost

00:11:38.150 --> 00:11:40.320 align:middle line:90%
city of Guayabo.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:44.090 align:middle line:84%
This is a city that was unknown
to the archeological world

00:11:44.090 --> 00:11:46.042 align:middle line:90%
until 25 years ago.

00:11:46.042 --> 00:11:50.367 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:50.367 --> 00:12:13.860 align:middle line:90%


00:12:13.860 --> 00:12:16.800 align:middle line:84%
One of the great mysteries
of Central America,

00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:21.270 align:middle line:84%
especially the area around
Costa Rica and Nicaragua,

00:12:21.270 --> 00:12:23.880 align:middle line:84%
is that we have
very little evidence

00:12:23.880 --> 00:12:31.550 align:middle line:84%
of organized city-states,
of planned communities.

00:12:31.550 --> 00:12:34.710 align:middle line:84%
And yet, here in the central
jungles of Costa Rica,

00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:37.156 align:middle line:90%
we find exactly that.

00:12:37.156 --> 00:12:41.638 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:41.638 --> 00:13:12.530 align:middle line:90%


00:13:12.530 --> 00:13:15.280 align:middle line:90%
We see this wide road.

00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:20.760 align:middle line:84%
We see these well-built
platforms on either side.

00:13:20.760 --> 00:13:23.910 align:middle line:84%
Yet this amazing city was
abandoned a few hundred years

00:13:23.910 --> 00:13:26.480 align:middle line:90%
before the Spanish arrived.

00:13:26.480 --> 00:13:30.550 align:middle line:84%
We don't know who the people
were who built this city.

00:13:30.550 --> 00:13:34.780 align:middle line:84%
We don't know where they went
or why they abandoned this city.

00:13:34.780 --> 00:13:38.405 align:middle line:84%
It's part of the mysteries of
Costa Rica and Central America.

00:13:38.405 --> 00:13:50.666 align:middle line:90%


00:13:50.666 --> 00:13:55.157 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:55.157 --> 00:14:09.129 align:middle line:90%


00:14:09.129 --> 00:14:13.121 align:middle line:90%
[THUNDER]

00:14:13.121 --> 00:14:44.630 align:middle line:90%


00:14:44.630 --> 00:14:47.630 align:middle line:84%
One of the problems with the
search for ancient technology

00:14:47.630 --> 00:14:51.290 align:middle line:84%
here in Central America
is, as you can see,

00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:54.640 align:middle line:84%
we're in a very
dense rainforest.

00:14:54.640 --> 00:14:57.020 align:middle line:84%
This makes it
extremely difficult

00:14:57.020 --> 00:15:01.270 align:middle line:84%
to preserve man-made
articles, especially metals

00:15:01.270 --> 00:15:03.780 align:middle line:90%
or artifacts made out of wood.

00:15:03.780 --> 00:15:09.280 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:16.780 align:middle line:90%


00:15:16.780 --> 00:15:20.780 align:middle line:90%
[THUNDER]

00:15:20.780 --> 00:15:33.280 align:middle line:90%


00:15:33.280 --> 00:15:35.070 align:middle line:84%
One of the other
interesting things

00:15:35.070 --> 00:15:37.500 align:middle line:84%
that we discovered in
Costa Rica is their use

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:39.790 align:middle line:90%
of tattooing and stamps.

00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:43.300 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, the various
Indians in Costa Rica

00:15:43.300 --> 00:15:48.640 align:middle line:84%
had all sorts of fancy
textiles and body painting,

00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:53.140 align:middle line:84%
as well as tattooing
with charcoal and parts

00:15:53.140 --> 00:15:54.400 align:middle line:90%
of their own blood.

00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:58.790 align:middle line:84%
This was used, of course,
in all the Pacific Islands.

00:15:58.790 --> 00:16:01.080 align:middle line:84%
It was also used
in Southeast Asia,

00:16:01.080 --> 00:16:04.920 align:middle line:84%
and in Arabia, and
among the Egyptians.

00:16:04.920 --> 00:16:10.250 align:middle line:84%
And here, in a 1529
book that was written

00:16:10.250 --> 00:16:14.020 align:middle line:84%
by Gonzalo Fernandez
De Oviedo, they

00:16:14.020 --> 00:16:16.380 align:middle line:84%
talk about the type
of tattooing that they

00:16:16.380 --> 00:16:18.950 align:middle line:90%
were doing in Costa Rica.

00:16:18.950 --> 00:16:22.050 align:middle line:84%
And he says here, all
the Indians of Nicoya,

00:16:22.050 --> 00:16:24.540 align:middle line:84%
and especially the
leaders and their women,

00:16:24.540 --> 00:16:27.860 align:middle line:84%
have their arms painted
in that black paint that

00:16:27.860 --> 00:16:32.230 align:middle line:84%
is made with their own blood
and with charcoal, cutting

00:16:32.230 --> 00:16:34.850 align:middle line:84%
and drawing first with
blades from the flint.

00:16:34.850 --> 00:16:38.820 align:middle line:90%


00:16:38.820 --> 00:16:42.350 align:middle line:84%
One of the other unusual
ancient technology mysteries

00:16:42.350 --> 00:16:44.900 align:middle line:84%
that we uncovered
in Central America

00:16:44.900 --> 00:16:47.790 align:middle line:84%
can also be found in this
book, "Sweat of the Sun

00:16:47.790 --> 00:16:51.680 align:middle line:84%
and the Tears of the
Moon," a book about gold

00:16:51.680 --> 00:16:55.430 align:middle line:90%
and silver pre-Columbian art.

00:16:55.430 --> 00:16:59.910 align:middle line:84%
Andre Emmerich was
a Swiss Costa Rican

00:16:59.910 --> 00:17:04.880 align:middle line:84%
who was fascinated by all
of the gold and jewelry that

00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:09.290 align:middle line:84%
was found in Costa Rica,
