genetically engineered

00:19:29.730 --> 00:19:33.150 align:middle line:84%
in remote antiquity to
be a seedless plant,

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:35.980 align:middle line:84%
like a seedless grape
or a seedless orange.

00:19:35.980 --> 00:19:41.090 align:middle line:84%
Bananas exist all over the
world, even on remote islands.

00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:43.400 align:middle line:84%
Bananas are one
of the few fruits

00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:47.140 align:middle line:84%
that you can live
completely on, with protein,

00:19:47.140 --> 00:19:51.900 align:middle line:84%
and carbohydrates, and
vitamins, and other minerals.

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:54.490 align:middle line:84%
Bananas are the
world's tallest grass.

00:19:54.490 --> 00:19:57.920 align:middle line:84%
But grass is normally
reproduced by seeds

00:19:57.920 --> 00:20:01.760 align:middle line:90%
and by tubers in their roots.

00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:06.200 align:middle line:84%
The banana, however, is unusual
in that the banana is only

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:09.010 align:middle line:84%
able to reproduce
through its roots

00:20:09.010 --> 00:20:13.010 align:middle line:84%
and through shoots and tubers,
not through the actual fruit

00:20:13.010 --> 00:20:14.610 align:middle line:90%
itself.

00:20:14.610 --> 00:20:17.880 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, there's an
indication that some time

00:20:17.880 --> 00:20:22.540 align:middle line:84%
in remote antiquity, the banana
was genetically engineered

00:20:22.540 --> 00:20:25.100 align:middle line:90%
to be a seedless fruit.

00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:30.494 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps it was engineered in
what we like to call Atlantis.

