One purpose is as a section of
a pillar to hold up a temple.

00:33:15.190 --> 00:33:21.530 align:middle line:84%
But it also has a metallic
mold carved into it.

00:33:21.530 --> 00:33:24.560 align:middle line:84%
And this mold would have
been used apparently

00:33:24.560 --> 00:33:31.290 align:middle line:84%
for making ax heads or even
possibly keystone clamps.

00:33:31.290 --> 00:33:36.060 align:middle line:84%
And we see how molten
metals would be poured

00:33:36.060 --> 00:33:39.600 align:middle line:90%
into these hourglass shapes.

00:33:39.600 --> 00:33:42.860 align:middle line:84%
We see a channel for the
metal to come through and pour

00:33:42.860 --> 00:33:48.276 align:middle line:84%
a second ax head,
an hourglass shape.

00:33:48.276 --> 00:33:58.750 align:middle line:84%
It's clearly been used for some
kind of metal manufacturing.

00:33:58.750 --> 00:34:01.760 align:middle line:84%
This itself is curious
because it indicates

00:34:01.760 --> 00:34:05.430 align:middle line:84%
that one of the things that
was going on here on Lake

00:34:05.430 --> 00:34:09.199 align:middle line:84%
Nicaragua, at Zapatera
Island, and on the mainland,

00:34:09.199 --> 00:34:13.600 align:middle line:84%
was some kind of
metallurgical industry.

00:34:13.600 --> 00:34:18.073 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:34:18.073 --> 00:34:31.900 align:middle line:90%


00:34:31.900 --> 00:34:36.949 align:middle line:84%
Many of these statues here are
in an unusual kneeling position

00:34:36.949 --> 00:34:39.659 align:middle line:90%
known as [INAUDIBLE].

00:34:39.659 --> 00:34:42.120 align:middle line:84%
We find this kneeling
position, which

00:34:42.120 --> 00:34:48.710 align:middle line:84%
is thought to be a symbol
of respect for authority,

00:34:48.710 --> 00:34:50.310 align:middle line:90%
here in Nicaragua.

00:34:50.310 --> 00:34:55.590 align:middle line:84%
We find it at statues at
Tiwanaku, on Lake Titicaca.

00:34:55.590 --> 00:34:58.520 align:middle line:84%
We find a statue like
this on Easter Island.

00:34:58.520 --> 00:35:01.980 align:middle line:84%
We find them in Egypt and
in the Hittite cities,

00:35:01.980 --> 00:35:05.880 align:middle line:90%
and in fact, all over the world.

00:35:05.880 --> 00:35:11.120 align:middle line:84%
This large basalt statue is
anthropomorphic in that it's

00:35:11.120 --> 00:35:14.996 align:middle line:84%
only of a man without any
apparent animal qualities.

00:35:14.996 --> 00:35:18.570 align:middle line:90%


00:35:18.570 --> 00:35:20.690 align:middle line:90%
Probably weighs several tons.

00:35:20.690 --> 00:35:25.430 align:middle line:84%
And even though it's been
defaced and extremely worn,

00:35:25.430 --> 00:35:27.840 align:middle line:84%
he appears to be
wearing a turban,

00:35:27.840 --> 00:35:31.440 align:middle line:84%
much as we see at
Titicaca, and Tiwanaku,

00:35:31.440 --> 00:35:35.551 align:middle line:84%
and of course, areas
of the Middle East.

00:35:35.551 --> 00:35:40.421 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:40.421 --> 00:35:45.300 align:middle line:90%


00:35:45.300 --> 00:35:49.740 align:middle line:84%
Each one of these
monolithic basalt statues

00:35:49.740 --> 00:35:52.960 align:middle line:90%
represents a piece of the past.

00:35:52.960 --> 00:35:57.440 align:middle line:84%
If we could only understand the
symbols and the meaning of each

00:35:57.440 --> 00:36:00.770 align:middle line:84%
of these statues, it
would help us unravel

00:36:00.770 --> 00:36:03.198 align:middle line:90%
the mysteries of Nicaragua.

00:36:03.198 --> 00:36:08.088 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:36:08.088 --> 00:36:20.810 align:middle line:90%


00:36:20.810 --> 00:36:24.000 align:middle line:84%
One of the interesting things
that they did here in Nicaragua

00:36:24.000 --> 00:36:29.440 align:middle line:84%
was the birdman
festival, where natives

00:36:29.440 --> 00:36:34.920 align:middle line:84%
got up on these long
poles with spinning ropes

00:36:34.920 --> 00:36:40.170 align:middle line:84%
and then spun around the pole
like a big Maypole birdman

00:36:40.170 --> 00:36:43.260 align:middle line:90%
flying festival.

00:36:43.260 --> 00:36:50.090 align:middle line:84%
This same unusual ritual also
takes place in Northeast Mexico

00:36:50.090 --> 00:36:51.778 align:middle line:90%
and at the ruins of Tajin.

00:36:51.778 --> 00:36:54.650 align:middle line:90%


00:36:54.650 --> 00:36:58.560 align:middle line:84%
There's many similarities
here in Nicaragua

00:36:58.560 --> 00:37:03.700 align:middle line:84%
with the discovery of the
Olmec civilization in Mexico

00:37:03.700 --> 00:37:06.280 align:middle line:90%
during the 1940s.

00:37:06.280 --> 00:37:10.470 align:middle line:84%
Both here in Nicaragua and
with the Olmecs in Mexico,

00:37:10.470 --> 00:37:14.550 align:middle line:84%
many of these giant
heads and basalt statues

00:37:14.550 --> 00:37:18.694 align:middle line:84%
were just found buried
in swamps and jungles.

00:37:18.694 --> 00:37:22.566 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:37:22.566 --> 00:37:24.502 align:middle line:90%


00:37:24.502 --> 00:37:27.810 align:middle line:84%
In both Nicaragua
and Costa Rica,

00:37:27.810 --> 00:37:33.970 align:middle line:84%
there were many fine examples of
ceramics, exquisite polychrome

00:37:33.970 --> 00:37:41.520 align:middle line:84%
pottery done in zoomorphic
figurines of crocodiles,

00:37:41.520 --> 00:37:47.610 align:middle line:84%
jaguars, and anthrozoomorphic
animal-man figures, some

00:37:47.610 --> 00:37:51.710 align:middle line:84%
of the finest ceramics
that we find in the world.

00:37:51.710 --> 00:37:54.100 align:middle line:84%
One of the mysteries
of Central America

00:37:54.100 --> 00:37:59.400 align:middle line:84%
is that the Mayans, and the
Mixtecs, and the Zapotecs

00:37:59.400 --> 00:38:01.030 align:middle line:90%
were farther north.

00:38:01.030 --> 00:38:04.460 align:middle line:84%
And it's not really believed
that they had much contact

00:38:04.460 --> 00:38:07.870 align:middle line:90%
with Nicaragua and Costa Rica.

00:38:07.870 --> 00:38:12.940 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, the Incas and
other South American cultures

00:38:12.940 --> 00:38:15.420 align:middle line:90%
were farther to the south.

00:38:15.420 --> 00:38:19.220 align:middle line:84%
So we have in Nicaragua
and Costa Rica something

00:38:19.220 --> 00:38:24.380 align:middle line:84%
of a null zone here
at the southern part

00:38:24.380 --> 00:38:28.610 align:middle line:84%
of North America that's not
really definitely connected

00:38:28.610 --> 00:38:32.050 align:middle line:84%
to any of the
known civilizations

00:38:32.050 --> 00:38:33.946 align:middle line:90%
that we're aware of.

00:38:33.946 --> 00:38:38.926 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

