00:42:00.328 --> 00:42:07.310 align:middle line:90%


00:42:07.310 --> 00:42:09.610 align:middle line:84%
Here on this pyramid
island that we've

00:42:09.610 --> 00:42:14.050 align:middle line:84%
found on the edge
of Lake Nicaragua,

00:42:14.050 --> 00:42:19.090 align:middle line:84%
are big walls with
huge basalt stones.

00:42:19.090 --> 00:42:24.210 align:middle line:84%
Some of these are definitely
weighing several tons.

00:42:24.210 --> 00:42:28.970 align:middle line:84%
There's no cement or really
indication of modern building

00:42:28.970 --> 00:42:30.270 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:42:30.270 --> 00:42:31.530 align:middle line:90%
But this is clearly man-made.

00:42:31.530 --> 00:42:34.230 align:middle line:90%


00:42:34.230 --> 00:42:35.960 align:middle line:90%
We don't know how old this is.

00:42:35.960 --> 00:42:39.870 align:middle line:84%
But someone has put
in a lot of effort

00:42:39.870 --> 00:42:44.560 align:middle line:84%
to build these walls that seem
to be part of this pyramid

00:42:44.560 --> 00:42:46.890 align:middle line:90%
island.

00:42:46.890 --> 00:42:49.610 align:middle line:84%
Exactly how old this
is, whether it's

00:42:49.610 --> 00:42:56.062 align:middle line:84%
only 50 years old or
5,000, we just don't know.

00:42:56.062 --> 00:43:00.020 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC  PLAYING]

00:43:00.020 --> 00:43:04.220 align:middle line:84%
Our next stop was the
Gulf area of Mexico,

00:43:04.220 --> 00:43:09.410 align:middle line:84%
the area around Villahermosa,
and Veracruz, and Xalapa.

00:43:09.410 --> 00:43:14.880 align:middle line:84%
This area is the heartland
of the mysterious Olmecs.

00:43:14.880 --> 00:43:20.180 align:middle line:84%
The Olmecs are one of the most
baffling of Central America's

00:43:20.180 --> 00:43:24.680 align:middle line:84%
cultures, and
probably the oldest.

00:43:24.680 --> 00:43:28.590 align:middle line:84%
Archeologists now
trace the Olmecs back

00:43:28.590 --> 00:43:33.100 align:middle line:90%
to at least 1,300 BC.

00:43:33.100 --> 00:43:37.280 align:middle line:84%
The Olmecs are known for
their colossal heads.

00:43:37.280 --> 00:43:44.100 align:middle line:84%
These are 20-ton
basalt giant heads

00:43:44.100 --> 00:43:48.840 align:middle line:84%
that are carved from one
of the hardest rocks known.

00:43:48.840 --> 00:43:51.490 align:middle line:90%
The carving is extremely fine.

00:43:51.490 --> 00:43:55.720 align:middle line:90%
It appears to be machined.

00:43:55.720 --> 00:43:59.640 align:middle line:84%
And that some kind
of power tools

00:43:59.640 --> 00:44:03.570 align:middle line:90%
were used on these basalt heads.

00:44:03.570 --> 00:44:06.840 align:middle line:84%
How they were
transported and brought

00:44:06.840 --> 00:44:11.090 align:middle line:84%
to various areas around the
Gulf of Mexico and Mexico

00:44:11.090 --> 00:44:12.780 align:middle line:90%
is a mystery.

00:44:12.780 --> 00:44:18.170 align:middle line:84%
And similarly, like the giant
stone balls of Costa Rica,

00:44:18.170 --> 00:44:21.510 align:middle line:84%
it's not really known what the
purpose of these giant heads

00:44:21.510 --> 00:44:24.190 align:middle line:84%
was and what they
were doing with them.

00:44:24.190 --> 00:44:26.610 align:middle line:84%
It's presumed that
they were somehow

00:44:26.610 --> 00:44:30.815 align:middle line:84%
the kings, the
chiefs of the Olmecs.

00:44:30.815 --> 00:44:35.094 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:44:35.094 --> 00:44:39.580 align:middle line:90%


00:44:39.580 --> 00:44:43.630 align:middle line:84%
Here we are in Xalapa, Mexico
in the state of Veracruz,

00:44:43.630 --> 00:44:45.780 align:middle line:90%
near the Gulf Coast.

00:44:45.780 --> 00:44:48.150 align:middle line:84%
It's here in this museum
that some of the finest

00:44:48.150 --> 00:44:51.360 align:middle line:90%
Olmec statues can be found.

00:44:51.360 --> 00:44:53.040 align:middle line:84%
The Olmecs are thought
to be the mother

00:44:53.040 --> 00:44:56.340 align:middle line:90%
culture of all of Mesoamerica.

00:44:56.340 --> 00:44:59.150 align:middle line:84%
But they are the most
mysterious of all

00:44:59.150 --> 00:45:02.252 align:middle line:90%
of Mexico's many civilizations.

00:45:02.252 --> 00:45:06.678 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45:06.678 --> 00:45:22.010 align:middle line:90%


00:45:22.010 --> 00:45:25.910 align:middle line:84%
In the early 1940s, University
of California archeologist

00:45:25.910 --> 00:45:31.420 align:middle line:84%
Matthew Stirling discovered
over five colossal Olmec heads

00:45:31.420 --> 00:45:38.170 align:middle line:84%
made out of granite, the
largest weighing over 24 tons.

00:45:38.170 --> 00:45:40.250 align:middle line:84%
It's a mystery how
the Olmecs were

00:45:40.250 --> 00:45:45.000 align:middle line:84%
able to move these giant heads
and other statues over 100

00:45:45.000 --> 00:45:49.810 align:middle line:84%
kilometers from the quarry to
their pyramid city at La Venta.

00:45:49.810 --> 00:45:51.730 align:middle line:84%
Archeologists assume
that the Olmecs

00:45:51.730 --> 00:45:55.660 align:middle line:90%
didn't know about the wheel.

00:45:55.660 --> 00:46:01.720 align:middle line:84%
The Olmecs are really a recent
discovery to archeologists.

00:46:01.720 --> 00:46:07.950 align:middle line:84%
Prior really to 1940,
archeologists and historians

00:46:07.950 --> 00:46:12.290 align:middle line:84%
did not recognize the Olmecs
and that they existed.

00:46:12.290 --> 00:46:19.450 align:middle line:84%
Certain art that was
coming out of Mexico

00:46:19.450 --> 00:46:21.700 align:middle line:90%
was noticed to be very unusual.

00:46:21.700 --> 00:46:26.600 align:middle line:84%
And in the 1930s, the
Smithsonian Institution

00:46:26.600 --> 00:46:30.750 align:middle line:84%
and the Museum of the
American Indian in New York,

00:46:30.750 --> 00:46:37.710 align:middle line:84%
they started realizing that some
of the artifacts that they were

00:46:37.710 --> 00:46:41.530 align:middle line:84%
getting were not
Mayan and couldn't

00:46:41.530 --> 00:46:47.200 align:middle line:84%
be ascribed to any of the
known cultures in Mexico.

00:46:47.200 --> 00:46:53.060 align:middle line:84%
Then in 1940, a huge
archeological conference

00:46:53.060 --> 00:46:55.480 align:middle line:90%
was held in Mexico City.

00:46:55.480 --> 00:46:59.410 align:middle line:84%
And in that conference,
Mexican archeologists

00:46:59.410 --> 00:47:02.950 align:middle line:84%
and American archeologists
presented evidence

00:47:02.950 --> 00:47:05.190 align:middle line:84%
to archeologists from
all over the world

00:47:05.190 --> 00:47:11.310 align:middle line:84%
that there was an older
culture than the Maya.

00:47:11.310 --> 00:47:17.120 align:middle line:84%
And this culture they called the
Olmecs, or the rubber people.

00:47:17.120 --> 00:47:21.440 align:middle line:84%
And in that conference,
they claimed

00:47:21.440 --> 00:47:24.130 align:middle line:84%
that the Olmecs were
the oldest of all

00:47:24.130 --> 00:47:27.720 align:middle line:90%
the cultures in Mesoamerica.

00:47:27.720 --> 00:47:30.730 align:middle line:84%
And that the Mayans,
and the Zapotecs,

00:47:30.730 --> 00:47:35.070 align:middle line:84%
and Mixtecs were all
coming ultimately

00:47:35.070 --> 00:47:39.790 align:middle line:84%
from this older culture, which
they then called the Olmecs.

00:47:39.790 --> 00:47:43.270 align:middle line:84%
So many questions
remain about the Olmecs.

00:47:43.270 --> 00:47:44.651 align:middle line:90%
Who were they?

00:47:44.651 --> 00:47:46.170 align:middle line:90%
Were they from Africa?

00:47:46.170 --> 00:47:47.570 align:middle line:90%
From Egypt?

00:47:47.570 --> 00:47:49.630 align:middle line:90%
From Atlantis?

00:47:49.630 --> 00:47:55.280 align:middle line:84%
We know that the Olmecs
are over 3,000 years old.

00:47:55.280 --> 00:47:56.710 align:middle line:90%
But what were they doing here?

00:47:56.710 --> 00:48:01.250 align:middle line:84%
Why were they carving
these giant heads?

00:48:01.250 --> 00:48:02.480 align:middle line:90%
Why did they move them?

00:48:02.480 --> 00:48:04.620 align:middle line:90%
What happened to them?

00:48:04.620 --> 00:48:07.810 align:middle line:84%
These are some of the
greatest mysteries of history.

00:48:07.810 --> 00:48:14.190 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

